audio_analysis.transcript: To give you an edge, here's a list of what every knight lord is weak against. Gladius is weak against Holy Damage and Pierce Weapons, as well as being greatly affected by sleep, rot, and bleed prox. A del is hindered by poison, rot, frostbite, and sleep prox. Both the Moth and the Scorpion of Noster are weak to fire damage, rot, bleed, and frostbite prox. Separately, the Moth is weaker to slash and piercing weapons, while the Scorpion is weaker to striking weapons. Marius is weak to lightning weapons, while being greatly affected by slashing weapons. Libra is weak to madness buildup, while being greatly hindered by holy, fire, and slashing weapons, as well as poison and rot being easily prox. Full Gore is weak to lightning weapons, as well as any status effect that isn't madness. Caligo is weak to fire damage and more susceptible to striking weapons, and last but not least, holster the knight lord is weak to holy damage. When he's in his first phase, fire, slashing, and piercing weapons deal more damage, but once he transitions to his second phase, he receives more damage from lightning, striking, and piercing weapons.
